🔥 1. Metasploitable (best starting point)
Created by Rapid7 (same people behind Metasploit)
Designed specifically to be hacked
Works perfectly with Metasploit Framework

Docker version:

docker run -it --rm -p 8080:80 tleemcjr/metasploitable2

👉 Vulnerabilities:

Old Apache, FTP, SSH
Weak credentials
Known CVEs (easy for practice)
🐳 2. DVWA (Damn Vulnerable Web App)
Great for web hacking (SQLi, XSS, CSRF)
docker run -d -p 8081:80 vulnerables/web-dvwa

Works well with Metasploit + manual testing.

💀 3. OWASP Juice Shop (modern + realistic)
Maintained by OWASP
More modern vulnerabilities than DVWA
docker run -d -p 3000:3000 bkimminich/juice-shop
🧪 4. Vulhub (huge collection)
Repo with many vulnerable environments
git clone https://github.com/vulhub/vulhub
cd vulhub
docker-compose up -d

👉 Includes:

Apache Struts exploits
Redis, Elasticsearch, etc.
Real-world CVEs
